EOS Instruction Manual Guide

For Superuser Account

 

 

Step-1: Access EOS URL ( Non-Azure Login ) -http://eosuat.southeastasia.cloudapp.azure.com/#/user/login

The below page will be displayed while accessing the EOS URL:

 

Step-2: Enter Superuser username and password to the EOS system.

 

Step-3: After successful login to EOS system, the main EOS page will open which will display the Transaction Overview for Dashboard feature.

 

Step-4: Superuser can see the list of features on the screen to access.

 

Step-5: Superuser can view their user profile by clicking on the user profile icon shown in below snapshot. User can also change their password or logout from here.

 

 

For Dashboard Features:

Step-1: Click on the Dashboard feature to view Transaction details.

 

Step-2: Upon clicking the EOS ID, which is link, user can view all the details of the particular transaction linked to that EOS ID.

 

 

Step-3: Clicking on the "return to previous page" will return you to the main window page of that feature.

Step-4: User can select the required options through dropdown box appearing. The summary of all transaction will be displayed for selected option.

Step-5: Click on "Reset" button to revert the changes made by selecting the options from dropdown box.

Step-6: User can view the number of transactions with their details while clicking on "No of Transaction" section on total, closed, open and cancelled and their percentage of status is also displayed in bar.

 

 

 

 

For Transaction Features:

Step-1: Click on the Transaction feature to view Summary of all Transaction.

 

 

Step-2: Click to "Expand" icon to view all the filter options as shown in below snapshot.

 

Step-3: User can select the required options through dropdown box appearing. Upon clicking on the "search" button, the summary of all transaction will be displayed for selected option.

Step-4: Click on "Reset" button to revert the changes made by selecting the options from dropdown box.

Step-5: Upon clicking the "EOS ID", the Transaction details linked to that EOS ID will be displayed as shown below. E.g., "EOS ID" – "E63"

 

 

Step-6: Clicking on the "return to previous page" will return you to the main window page of that feature.

Step-7: To Print the details of the Transaction, user need to select the "EOS ID", then click on "Print" button. User will be able to print the details.

 

Step-8: To download the details of the Transaction in csv, user need to select the "EOS ID", then click on "CSV" button. User will be able to download the transaction details in csv format in their desktop.

 

 

 

 

Step-9: User can also sort in ascending, descending or unsort the sorted data for the fields that select for this activity. There are sorting button available with the columns name.

 

Step-10: User can also modify the details of the transactions by clicking on the "modify" icon in "option" field. Below page will be displayed to alert the details: 

 

 

 

 

 

 

Step-11: User can also delete the transactions record by clicking on the delete icon in "option" field. Below message will pop-up and while clicking on "OK" button that record will be deleted. 

 

Step-12: Click on "Create New" to create a new Transaction. Below page will appear where user can add the required values. Click "OK" to add new transaction.

 

For Threshold Features:

Step-1: Click on Threshold Feature, Superuser will see two dropdown option for "Summary" and "Triggered Alerts". Click on "Summary" and below "Threshold Limit List" will appear.

 

Step-2: Click to "Expand" icon to view all the filter options as shown in below snapshot.

 

Step-3: User can select the required options through dropdown box appearing. Upon clicking on the "search" button, the summary of Threshold limit list will be displayed for selected option.

Step-4: Click on "Reset" button to revert the changes made by selecting the options from dropdown box.

Step-5: To Print the details of the Threshold list, user need to select the "Threshold ID", then click on "Print" button. User will be able to print the details.

User can select one or more than one "Threshold ID" to print at the same time.

 

Step-6: User can also modify the details of the threshold by clicking on the "modify" icon in "option" field. Below page will be displayed to alert the details:

 

Step-7: User can also delete the threshold limit record by clicking on the delete icon in "option" field. Below message will pop-up and while clicking on "OK" button that record will be deleted.

 

Step-8: Click on "Create New" to create a new Threshold limit setting. Below page will appear where user can add the required values.

 

Step-9: User can also sort in ascending, descending or unsort the sorted data for the fields that select for this activity. There are sorting button available with the columns name.

 

Step-10: Click on "Triggered Alerts" within Threshold Feature. Below "Threshold Triggered Alerts" will appear.

 

Step-11: Click to "Expand" icon to view all the filter options as shown in below snapshot.

 

Step-12: User can select the required options through dropdown box appearing. Upon clicking on the "search" button, the "Threshold Triggered Alerts" list will be displayed for selected option.

Step-13: Click on "Reset" button to revert the changes made by selecting the options from dropdown box.

Step-14: Click on the "Alert ID" and this will redirect the user to the transaction details of that linked to the selected Alert ID. Below page will appear:

 

 

Step-15: Clicking on the "return to previous page" will return you to the main window page of Triggered Alerts.

Step-16: User can add the remarks/notes in the "Remarks" column by clicking on the modify icon and below page will appear.

 

Step-17: User can also sort in ascending, descending or unsort the sorted data for the fields that select for this activity. There are sorting button available with the columns name.

 

 

 

 

 

For Information Page Feature:

Step-1: Click on Information Page Feature, user will see the dropdown option for "Jetty Criteria" Click on "Jetty Criteria" and below Jetty Information will appear.

 

 

 

 

Step-2: Upon clicking the "Jetty No", user will see the display of the Jetty information. Refer below snapshot.

 

Step-3: User can also sort in ascending, descending or unsort the sorted data for the fields that select for this activity. There are sorting button available with the columns name.

 

Step-4: Upon selecting one or more than one "Jetty No", a "batch deletion" button appear at the end of the screen to allow superusers to delete those records as shown in below snapshot:

 

Step-5 : User can also modify the details of the Jetty by clicking on the "modify" icon in "option" field. Below page will be displayed to alert the details:

 

Step-6: User can also delete the Jetty record by clicking on the delete icon in "option" field. Below message will pop-up and while clicking on "OK" button that record will be deleted.

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

For Report Feature: 

Step-1: Upon clicking on the Report Feature, user will see the Report History page.

 

Step-2: Click to "Expand" icon to view all the filter options as shown in below snapshot.

 

Step-3: User can select/enter the required options through dropdown box appearing for the selection. Upon clicking on the "search" button, the Reports details will be displayed for selected option.

Step-4: Click on "Reset" button to revert the changes made by selecting the options from dropdown box.

 

 

 

 

Step-5: User can also sort in ascending, descending or unsort the sorted data for the fields that select for this activity. There are sorting button available with the columns name.

 

Step-6: User can click on the "Report Name" which is clickable link, a new page will appear with details of that report name selected. E.g: Selected Report Name is "Transaction Summary (monthly)".

 

 

 

 

Step-7: To Print the details of the Report selected, user need to check/select the records that they want to print, then click on "Print" button. User will be able to print the details.

User can select one or more than one records to print at the same time.

 

Step-8: To download the details of the Report in csv, user need to select the records, then click on "CSV" button. User will be able to download the report details in csv format in their desktop.

 

Step-9: Clicking on the "return to previous page" will return you to the main window page of Report History.

Step-10: User can also see the Template Information, upon clicking on the "Template Used" record and the template information will be displayed as shown below.

If there are no template name provided, then it will appear as "-"  which is also clickable to see the template information.

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

Step-11: User can also delete the report record from Report History page by clicking on the delete icon on "Option" column. Below message will pop-up and while clicking on "OK" button that record will be deleted.

 

Step-12: User can also create a new report by clicking on the "Create New". Users need to select/enter the required details which is needed to create a new report.

 

 

 

Step-13: Clicking on "Generate Report", will help users to generate a new report and new page will open with generated records of report.

Step-14: Clicking on "Save Template", will help users to save the template.

Step-3: Click on "Reset" button to revert the changes made by selecting the options from dropdown box.

Step-5: To Print the details of the Users selected, user need to check/select the records that they want to print, then click on "Print" button. User will be able to print the details.

User can select one or more than one records to print at the same time.

 

Step-6: To download the details of the API Activity Log in csv, user need to select the records, then click on "CSV" button.

Step-7: Upon selecting the "No" on transaction flow screen, Superuser can see "batch deletion" box appearing at the end of page where Superuser can delete one or more records.
